# Go Notes Service

A Go REST API for managing notes and tasks.

## Tech Stack

- Go `1.25`
- Fiber `v2`
- GORM
- PostgreSQL or MySQL (selected by environment variable)

## Project Structure

- `cmd/server/main.go`: Application bootstrap and route registration
- `internal/db`: Database connection setup
- `internal/models`: Data models (`Note`, `Task`)
- `internal/repository`: Data access layer
- `internal/services`: Business logic layer
- `internal/handlers`: HTTP handlers
- `internal/routes`: Route mapping
- `frontend/index.html`: Simple UI served by the backend

## Prerequisites

- Go 1.25+
- A running database:
	- PostgreSQL, or
	- MySQL

## Database Configuration

Database selection is controlled by `DB_TYPE`:

- `postgres` (default if `DB_TYPE` is not set)
- `mysql`

Current DSNs are hardcoded in `internal/db/db.go`:

- Postgres: `host=localhost user=postgres password=admin dbname=notesdb port=5432 sslmode=disable`
- MySQL: `user:password@tcp(localhost:3306)/notesdb?charset=utf8mb4&parseTime=True&loc=Local`

If your local credentials are different, update the DSN constants in `internal/db/db.go`.

## Run the App (Windows PowerShell)

### Option 1: PostgreSQL laptop

```powershell
$env:DB_TYPE='postgres'
go run .\cmd\server\main.go
```

### Option 2: MySQL laptop (if no PostgreSQL installed)

```powershell
$env:DB_TYPE='mysql'
go run .\cmd\server\main.go
```

Server starts on `http://localhost:8080`.

## Frontend

The app serves `frontend/index.html` as static content via Fiber static middleware.

- Open: `http://localhost:8080/`

## API Endpoints

### Notes

- `POST /notes`
- `GET /notes`
- `GET /notes/:id`
- `PUT /notes/:id`
- `DELETE /notes/:id`

Example body for create/update:

```json
{
	"title": "Shopping",
	"content": "Buy milk"
}
```

### Tasks

- `POST /tasks`
- `GET /tasks`
- `GET /tasks/:id`
- `PUT /tasks/:id`
- `DELETE /tasks/:id`

Example body for create/update:

```json
{
	"title": "Daily workout",
	"description": "30 minutes cardio",
	"completed": false
}
```

## Test

```powershell
go test ./...
```

## Notes

- This project currently does not include an in-memory repository mode.
- For machine-to-machine consistency, prefer running a local DB container (Postgres/MySQL) with the matching `DB_TYPE`.
